C4a_neededhealthcarebutdidnotreceivespec: I found that the information I received from the Neurologist and my physician re treatment and medication was in conflict.  By contacting Parkinson's Canada during COVID-19 and speaking to client services ,I was relieved of much stress and anxiety regarding my condition.  I do realize that physicians do no have the time to address all issues related to a Parkinson's diagnosis.  I would hope that ALL specialists and physicians inform their Parkinson's patients to call Parkinson's Canada to get all the necessary information to go forward regarding treatment and medication.  The person I spoke to (ShanNo Harrison) at Parkinson's Canada in Ottawa was not rushed or impatient in providing me with important information i.e. physiotherapist, support group,virtual exercise programmes and so much more.

C4a_neededhealthcarebutdidnotreceivespec: All of my activities at the day center have been canceled. I had to wait more than 6 months to receive my wheelchair. I canceled my weekly bath service during the pandemic - when I tried to start over I was put back on a waiting list and reassessed (by phone) my situation - as if I was to improve ... yet I was told that we would start the baths again as soon as I asked. I have just been told that baths are not an essential service ... I am unable to do it on my own - I even have difficulty brushing my teeth. My social worker was on sick leave, I was assigned someone new and finally when my primary social worker returned, I was not notified. I only received one call from the CLSC during the pandemic. I felt isolated and my physical and mental ability greatly diminished.
C7_ideastoimproveaccess: Appointments with doctor and neurologist as well as social worker should be done on FaceTime or Zoom - where you can see my deterioration. My wife had to answer their question because I have great difficulty expressing myself - Indeed, it is she who helps me to write these comments.
